		<h4><div>James Sommerville and Patricia Evans<br>to perform double horn concerto</div></h4>
		<p>James Sommerville has been on our stage before, but not for quite a while. Back in &lsquo;99, Sommerville was just starting out as a horn player and we called him &lsquo;Jamie!&rsquo;</p>
		<p>Now James is the principal horn player for the Boston Symphony Orchestra and Music Director & Conductor of the Hamilton Philharmonic Orchestra. At this concert, we&rsquo;ll see both sides of this accomplished musician.</p>
		<p>Sommerville will conduct the entire concert, will be horn soloist in Mozart&rsquo;s E-flat Major Horn Concerto and will then double up with WSO principal horn player Patricia Evans for a rare treat: Beethoven&rsquo;s Sextet in E-flat for Two Horns.</p>
		<p><b>Karen Sunabacka</b></p>
		<p>We&rsquo;re pleased to be presenting another new work by Winnipeg-born composer Karen Sunabacka. Last season&rsquo;s charming <i>Born by the River</i> was a genuine crowd-pleaser!</p>
		<p>In addition to her work as a composer and cellist, Karen runs a private cello studio and manages a full time teaching load at Providence University College in Otterburne, Manitoba, where she founded the Providence Performing Arts School.</p>

